</b></p>
<p><b>Report of the Open-ended Working Group on an optional protocol to the 
International Covenant on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights on its  
        fifth session (Geneva, 4-8 February and 31 March-4 April 2008) 
</b></p>
<p><b>Corrigendum 
</b></p>
<p><b>1. Paragraph 12 
</b></p>
<p>The first sentence <i>should read</i> 
</p>
<p>In view of the severe resource constraints faced by developing countries, Bangladesh, China, 
Egypt (on behalf of the African Group), the Libyan Arab Jamahiriya, Amnesty International and 
CETIM supported including a provision on international assistance and cooperation.  
</p>
<p><b>2. Paragraph 144 
</b></p>
<p>The last sentence <i>should read</i> 
</p>
<p>Argentina, China and India stated that Part I of the Covenant should be excluded from the scope 
of the article. 
</p>
